SCSI_TestReady  (?)
#Parent SCSI_
=>	R1 =	drive number
<=	R0 =	1 if spun down, 2 if spun up

This SWI will check for the 'readiness' of a SCSI drive. If a SCSI disc is not spun up, the first access will give the error 'SCSI disc not ready', and the disc will be spun up.
# Gerph> Found by experimentation.
